Statistical analysis of EEG data was performed using custom R scripts and the “lmertest” package26, which allows fitting linear mixed-effects model and uses Satterthwaite’s approximation to degrees of freedom, to determine the F statistics of the fixed effects. Alpha power changes were averaged across electrodes over different topographical regions (frontal, central, occipital, temporal/parietal; Fig. S2A). Alpha asymmetry was measured as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
